deck: A 4 part comic book mini series based on the professional wrestling franchise of the same name.
description:
Plot Summary

Beginning with a recap of Team Death reigning supreme at the end of Ultima Lucha, then flashing forward to Catrina telling the Disciples of Death that they have to acquire the components for Mil Muertes’ throne. The Disciples begin this by murdering a group of mariachis.

Catrina meets with King Cuerno. Catrina propositions Cuerno to go after Fenix. The Disciples kill many people and then go after Big Rick, who is able to fight them off. Mil Muertes appears and murders Big Rick.

Using the skulls of their victims, the Disciples create a throne and then a dark energy descends upon The Temple. Mil Muertes, the King of Death, ascend his throne with his title belt while the Disciples continue their murderous spree and Catrina plots in Dario Cueto's office.

Note

Though the cover notes #1, this is indeed the second issue of the series as it was released 2 weeks after Peace Keeper.
name: The Throne

Born of the true north and tested in war, Captain Canuck is thrust into battle at the head of the global crisis intervention agency, Equilibrium. He must find his way as a warrior, leader and ultimately a hero to save humanity from the machinations of Mr. Gold and Blue Fox, as well as the even more menacing forces that watch in the shadows.

description:
A Lord of the Runes has the honour of fighting for his clan. In the event of conflict or dispute, this avoids a bloodbath between the fortress-states. Two fighters, one winner, and then the conflict is over.

Redwin is a teenage Dwarf of the Order of the Forge. He wants to become the Lord of the Runes of his clan against the wishes of his father. Unable to bear the humiliation of his father being called a coward, he decides nonetheless to become Lord of the Runes by his own means. The ensuing initiation rites include not only the art of forging arms, but also that of fighting... To become a Lord of the Runes, Redwin will confront a thousand warriors, including Rom who shares the same ambition. He will lose a lot, his soul, and his father in the pursuit of his obsession.
name: Redwin of the Forge 2/2

description: The 2016 election cycle is fast becoming one of the most interesting – and most divisive – in history. Clinton. Bush. Trump. Sanders. Paul. All strong personalities vying for the attention of the electorate. From the wild statements loudly announced by Trump to the frustrated uttering of Jeb and the defiant proclamations from Sanders, this volume explores the rise of those who lead the United States.

From the titanic terror team that brings you Haunted Horror and Weird Love comes a macabre mash-up of both hit series! Haunted Love features rotting tales of supernatural Pre-code romance from putrid horror comics from the vile horror comics of the 1950s. Lurid lust! Vicious violence! Creepy kisses! The zombie-fied Haunted Love #1 is just the first of 3 throbbing issues that will set your horrid hearts afire. Haunted Love will make your Valentines Day massacre and gory gift giving to your vile Valentine unforgettable and unforgivable.

1936. In the midst of a Europe which has been at peace for 75 years, a new city ermerges unlike any other in the world: Metropolis, the capital of excess and urban delirium. It is the focal point of numerous political movements and artistic trends as well as the nerve center for various forms of espionage and other underhanded activities. The citizens of Metropolis speak of nothing else but the horrible crimes plaguing the poorest parts of the city. To solve these crimes, the police have called upon an Austrian doctor, the inventor of a little-known field of science involving the treatment of the mind: a certain Doctor Freud.

TORONTO'S SUPERHEROES - UNITED AT LAST! The Human-Lizard is back, along with Mother Wonder, Majestic Rat, and Lady Accident as they stop some familiar foes known as the Frustrated Four from destroying the historic bargain store, Honest Ed's!

Note: The digital edition (2/17/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Zack sneaks into Principal Belding's office to run an after-hours poker game. When the blame gets pinned on Belding and he's fired for "gambling on school grounds," Zack can run wild with no one to keep him in line! He skips class to go surfing, misses quizzes, and does whatever he wants. With Belding out and Zack on the loose, can he turn Bayside into one big party?

Meet the SHIKARI FORCE: HUNTERS. There's Nil, an assassin and demon hunter who's dating Meena, the daughter of a demon. There's Jimi, a brilliant scientist who's not sure if he's going to save the world or destroy it. And finally, there is a renegade goddess from the age of legends. This team of misfits is out to hunt and destroy the Nagas, an ancient serpent race who want to reclaim earth from humanity with a diabolical secret weapon.

Everyone has their reason for walking away from a fight. Everyone has their reason for starting one too. As McQuade and Abe continue traveling around the country reassembling the team, they find truth in the old adage, the more things change, the more things stay the same. In this issue we see what Angel, Stonewall, and Blink have been up to since faking their deaths during the early days of the Iraq War. Join us for the fourth issue of George Pelicanos' shoot-till-the-clips-empty thrill ride, SIX.

It's underwater adventure as Dive-Clops and his aquatic battle tank, Dive Bomber, take on mysterious denizens of the deep who are threatening to submerge all of Skylands! The "eyes" have it as deep-water doom looms!

description:
The Epic Conclusion! From Wes Craven, the legendary icon that changed the face of cinema, and Steve Niles comes the final chapter in Craven's original comic book series. "Ritchie's rise from idle ignorance to a young man/young vampire with a deep knowledge of the world, both the good and the bad, is fascinating to me. And that he finds his place, his mission to be something we can actually admire. He and his two friends will not be predators of the innocent. But they will be hunters - hunters of evil. And when they ferret it out they will do battle with it to the death, until the world is just a bit safer for the rest of us." - Wes Craven
